From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 07:26:12 -1000
Subject: [PATCH 58/58] clang-mg: compact record layout optimizer (compact /
 hot / cold)

Add `compact`, a record modifier under -fcxxmg that reorders a struct/class/
union's non-static data members at compile time to produce the smallest correct
layout, while keeping field identity intact (member access, initialization, and
aliasing behave normally). `compact`, `hot`, and `cold` are keywords only under
-fcxxmg; otherwise they remain ordinary identifiers.

Layout
  - Padding minimization via descending effective-alignment packing, which is
    provably minimal when each field's size is a multiple of its alignment (all
    standard types). An exhaustive search runs only for the alignas-with-holes
    case (<=8 reorderable fields), so the common path stays O(n).
  - `hot` fields are pulled toward the first cache line; `cold` fields go to the
    tail. Declaration order is always kept as a candidate, so plain `compact`
    (no hot/cold, no atomics) is never larger than declaration order.
  - Atomic false-sharing isolation: _Atomic / std::atomic / std::atomic_flag
    fields are each placed on their own cache line. Detection is transitive
    through value members, bases, and arrays (not pointers). std::atomic_ref is
    excluded: it accesses external storage, so isolating the field would not
    isolate the referenced object.
  - Cache-line size configurable via -fcxxmg-cache-line=N (default 64; 0 opts
    out). The value is validated and normalized: non-powers-of-two round up with
    a warning, oversized values are rejected, so the bytes->bits conversion
    cannot overflow.

Whole-program / profile-guided layout
  - -fcxxmg-field-profile-use=<path> drives hot/cold placement from a usage
    profile keyed by (record name, field name-or-index); explicit markers win.
    Covers the keyword, `using`, and template-instantiation paths. The layout is
    a deterministic function of (declaration, profile file) -- ABI-safe across a
    consistent build.

Diagnostics (advisory unless noted)
  - -Rcxxmg-field-usage: per-field hot/warm/cold reference histogram with offset
    and enclosing record name (loop-nesting weighted).
  - -Rcxxmg-compact-summary: per-record byte-yield report.
  - -Rcxxmg-suggest-hot: most-referenced unmarked field; flags cold-on-hottest.
  - -Wcxxmg-compact: warns layout-observing escapes (offsetof, pointer cast,
    memcpy/memmove, structured bindings, std::bit_cast).
  - -Wcxxmg-compact-grows: reports intentional growth from hot/cold/atomics.
  - Positional aggregate init of a compact struct is rejected; the diagnostic
    names `compact` (it reuses the IsRandomized machinery but no longer leaks
    "randomized" wording).

Interop
  - Composes with conditional members, templates, type-expression generated
    records (`compact using C = A + B;`, including templated aliases). Orthogonal
    to the trait/implements system (matching is by name+type, not field order).

Implementation reuses Clang's existing record-layout machinery: the reorder runs
through RecordDecl::reorderDecls before layout, mirroring Randstruct. The core
packer lives in clang/lib/AST/CXXMGLayout.cpp.

diff --git a/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h b/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..817eaa287
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h
@@ -0,0 +1,85 @@
+//===- CXXMGLayout.h - C++MG compact record layout ------------*- C++ -*-===//
+//
+// Part of the LLVM Project, under the Apache License v2.0 with LLVM Exceptions.
+// See https://llvm.org/LICENSE.txt for license information.
+// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
+//
+//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
+//
+// This file declares the C++MG `compact` record-layout optimization: a
+// compile-time, opt-in transform that reorders a record's non-static data
+// members to minimize padding. It is the foundation for the optional `hot`/
+// `cold` field-placement refinements added in later increments.
+//
+//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
+
+#ifndef LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
+#define LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
+
+#include "llvm/ADT/STLFunctionalExtras.h"
+
+namespace clang {
+class ASTContext;
+class FieldDecl;
+class RecordDecl;
+
+namespace cxxmg {
+
+/// Field-placement hint requested by the C++MG `hot` / `cold` field markers.
+enum class CXXMGHotness : unsigned char {
+  None = 0, ///< Unmarked field: ordered purely to minimize padding.
+  Hot = 1,  ///< `hot`: pack toward the first cache line(s).
+  Cold = 2, ///< `cold`: push toward the tail.
+};
+
+/// Apply the C++MG `compact` layout to \p RD: reorder its fields to minimize
+/// padding (a stable sort by descending alignment) and commit the new order
+/// through RecordDecl::reorderDecls.
+///
+/// This must be called once \p RD is a complete definition but before its
+/// memory layout has been computed (i.e. before the first getASTRecordLayout
+/// query), so the layout builder observes the optimized declaration order.
+///
+/// The transform is conservative and is skipped (returning false, leaving the
+/// record untouched) when reordering would be unsafe or pointless: unions,
+/// dependent records, records with bases or a vptr, bitfields, anonymous
+/// members, or fewer than two reorderable fields.
+///
+/// Optional `hot`/`cold` field markers refine the order: `hot` fields are
+/// placed first (toward the first cache line(s)) and `cold` fields last, with
+/// padding minimized within each group. \p GetHotness returns the hint for a
+/// given field (CXXMGHotness::None for unmarked fields).
+///
+/// \returns true if the record's field order was changed.
+bool applyCompactLayout(
+    const ASTContext &Context, RecordDecl *RD,
+    llvm::function_ref<CXXMGHotness(const FieldDecl *)> GetHotness);
+
+/// Record that \p RD is a dependent `compact` template pattern, so each of its
+/// instantiations is reordered at Sema::ActOnFields. State is keyed by \p Context
+/// (per translation unit / AST), so it never leaks across contexts.
+void markCompactPattern(const ASTContext &Context, const RecordDecl *RD);
+
+/// Whether \p RD was recorded as a `compact` template pattern in \p Context.
+bool isCompactPattern(const ASTContext &Context, const RecordDecl *RD);
+
+/// Record/query the source-level `hot`/`cold` marker for a field, keyed by
+/// \p Context. Used so a `compact` template pattern's markers can be applied to
+/// each instantiation (which has distinct FieldDecls) at Sema::ActOnFields.
+void markFieldHotness(const ASTContext &Context, const FieldDecl *FD,
+                      CXXMGHotness Hotness);
+CXXMGHotness getFieldHotness(const ASTContext &Context, const FieldDecl *FD);
+
+/// Look up \p FD's hot/cold bucket in the field-usage profile named by
+/// -fcxxmg-field-profile-use (LangOptions::CXXMGFieldProfileFile). The profile
+/// is keyed by (enclosing record name, field source index) and is loaded once
+/// per \p Context and cached. Returns CXXMGHotness::None when no profile is
+/// configured, the file is unreadable, or the field has no profile entry. This
+/// is a deterministic function of the profile file, so every translation unit
+/// given the same profile derives the same layout (ABI-safe by construction).
+CXXMGHotness lookupFieldProfile(const ASTContext &Context, const FieldDecl *FD);
+
+} // namespace cxxmg
+} // namespace clang
+
+#endif // LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
